.TH "gen_pool_dma_zalloc_algo" 9 "gen_pool_dma_zalloc_algo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_pool_dma_zalloc_algo \- allocate special zeroed memory from the pool for DMA usage with the given pool algorithm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" gen_pool_dma_zalloc_algo
.BI "(struct gen_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma "  ","
.BI "genpool_algo_t algo "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool to allocate from
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to allocate from the pool
.IP "dma" 12
DMA-view physical address return value. Use NULL if unneeded.
.IP "algo" 12
algorithm passed from caller
.IP "data" 12
data passed to algorithm
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate the requested number of zeroed bytes from the specified pool. Uses
the given pool allocation function. Can not be used in NMI handler on
architectures without NMI-safe cmpxchg implementation.
.SH "RETURN"
virtual address of the allocated zeroed memory, or NULL on failure
